 By Chinonso Alozie
The 2019 governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Hope Uzodinma, yesterday, called on the people of Imo state, not to panic over the judgement of the governorship election tribunal delivered in Abuja, in favour of governor Emeka Ihedioha of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP. Uzodinma said in Owerri, that there are still other legal avenues to pursue his matter in the interest of the state. It was Uzodinma’s view that his team of lawyers are currently studying the outcome of the judgment and would communicate to his people soon. Continue reading Tribunal: Don’t panic, Uzodinma urges Imolites at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard